content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide a solution.

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure has 4 distinct layers
- Base layer: A red curved block with two U-shaped indentations
- Second layer: A blue cubic block in the center
- Third layer: A green rectangular block
- Top layer: An orange triangular/roof-shaped block

Block count: 4 total blocks

Spatial relationships:
- The red base block is horizontal and sits at the bottom
- The blue cube sits centered on the red base block
- The green rectangular block lies horizontally on top of the blue cube
- The orange triangular block sits centered on top of the green block

Required blocks from dictionary:
- Base: Block #1 (red U-shaped block)
- Middle: Block #4 (blue cube)
- Upper middle: Block #11 (horizontal green rectangle)
- Top: Block #15 (orange triangular/roof piece)

Assembly order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 4
    Step3: Move block with index 11
    Step4: Move block with index 15
}

This sequence will build the structure from bottom to top, ensuring stability during construction.
